        {
          "id": "elW693MdfK6M1c2pkK6x",
          "description": "🌟 I'm excited to introduce a leveled reading course that turns learning into a fun adventure! This course is about more than reading. It builds confidence, curiosity, and thinking skills, one great book at a time.\n\n✨ Foundations for Young Readers (Levels A–J)\nWe start with the basics: learning sounds, sight words, and understanding stories. Your child will enjoy fun, simple stories with pictures. They will practice following the words, guessing what happens next, and remembering story details. This builds a strong reading base.\n\n🚀 Becoming More Independent (Levels K–P)\nAs stories get longer, skills grow too! We read longer fiction and nonfiction books. This improves reading speed and introduces important skills like comparing stories and summarizing. Watch their vocabulary grow as they find main ideas and read with feeling!\n\n📚 Learning to Think Critically (Levels Q–Z)\nNow, students learn to analyze deeper themes, special language, and the author's goal. They will combine information from different texts, support their opinions with proof, and practice close reading—changing from learners to thinkers.\n\n🎯 Skills That Grow With Your Child\nEvery level practices core skills while adding new challenges:\n- Early Readers: Predict, connect to self, and check understanding.\n- Developing Readers: Summarize, read between the lines, and use text structure.\n- Advanced Readers: Evaluate, discuss, and use thinking strategies.\n\n💡 Why It Works\nWith support that slowly decreases—from guided help to independent reading—your child moves smoothly from learning to read to reading to learn. Best of all, they will enjoy every step thanks to interesting books and fun, interactive methods.\n\nReady to open a world of stories, knowledge, and confidence? Let's begin! 📖",
          "hourlyRate": 35.2,
